 visual stimulation to correct.<\/p>\n\n<p>There are probably many reasons why optometrists use a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pinhole_occluder\" rel=\"nofollow\">pinhole occluder<\/a> for diagnostic purposes, but never prescribe it as treatment...<\/p>\n","answer_id":2996,"question_id":2975,"up_vote_count":1}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/2975/what-negative-effects-can-pinhole-glasses-have-on-the-body","last_activity_date":1381755503,"creation_date":1343059374,"answer_count":1,"title":"What negative effects can pinhole glasses have on the body?","body":"<p>While shopping in the local supermarket yesterday, I was surprised to find this display on one of the shelves.<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/477t6.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/p>\n\n<p>I also realize that I should have taken a pamphlet with me, as well as a picture of the boxes for the glasses, as seen in the picture to read more about it.<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://skeptics.stackexchange.com/questions/7648/do-raster-glasses-work-for-improving-eyesight\">This answer at Skeptics.SE<\/a> shows that there are in fact probably no long-term benefits of wearing pinhole glasses, but my question is...<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>What potential harm/side effects can be caused in the short and long-term from wearing this type of eyewear?<\/strong><\/p>\n","question_id":2975,"tags":["human-anatomy","eyes","vision"],"score":2,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":2790,"up_vote_count":2,"last_edit_date":1343060183},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4277666449f41474561f867f04f32b73?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":158,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/158/harpalss","reputation":1335,"display_name":"harpalss","accept_rate":74},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8729233d525a654914051bf8c1234c78?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":115,"li