er_id":1590,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1590/rg255","reputation":11513,"display_name":"rg255","accept_rate":66},"score":3,"is_accepted":true,"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1381229399,"creation_date":1381229399,"body":"<blockquote>\n  <p>a) stronger aggressive behaviour only during egg laying<\/p>\n  \n  <p>c) stronger aggression when egg is first laid than during nest building<\/p>\n  \n  <p>d) greater aggression during hatching eggs than during nest building<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>These all occur after the stage which determines fitness. Egg laying (a and c) and Egg hatching (d) occur after the male has won the right to mate.<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>b) stronger aggressive behaviour during nest building rather than\n  during hatching of eggs<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>Assuming the behavior increases mating success and fitness, the answer is B because this is the only strategy that attracts more females and gets rid of rival males before it is too late (i.e. before the female mates). This is also assuming that the female can/will only mate once.<\/p>\n\n<p>In chronological order the answers run \"B,C/A,D\" (C &amp; A are really one and the same in my eyes). Mating occurs between B and C.<\/p>\n","answer_id":10778,"question_id":10679,"up_vote_count":3}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/10679/male-behaviour-during-breeding-season","last_activity_date":1381229399,"creation_date":1380737046,"answer_count":1,"title":"Male behaviour during breeding season","body":"<p>The mountain blue bird build nests to attract females and exhibit aggression towards other males during breeding season. Which of the following is likely to give the birds maximal evolutionary fitness?<\/p>\n\n<p>a) stronger aggressive behaviour only during egg laying <\/p>\n\n<p>b) stronger aggressive behaviour during nest building rather than during hatching of eggs<\/p>\n\n<p>c) stronger aggression when egg is first laid than during nest building<\/p>\n\