between so-called identical twins.  Besides, we've known for years that identical twins can have major epigenetic differences, so this isn't particularly ground-breaking.<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>If we assume that identical twins are exactly identical, then if we make a clone of a twin, will all three be exactly identical?<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>Depends on your definition of \"clone\" but how identical is identical?  If you mean exact, then probably not; at the very least they will have different numbers of cells, for example, not to even mention CNV or epigenetics.  If you want some SciFi cloning thing then, well, join the club.<\/p>\n","answer_id":10545,"question_id":10544,"up_vote_count":4},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/7a3d5e685f9dcf3ff8446127d44cd226?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":4527,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4527/khhsocratica","reputation":21,"display_name":"khhsocratica"},"score":2,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/iFDOX.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4216,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4216/ram-manohar-m","reputation":789,"display_name":"Ram Manohar M","accept_rate":31},"score":0,"post_id":10546,"edited":false,"creation_date":1380091653,"comment_id":14033,"body":"@ biogirl: Why clone? There are quite a number of monozygotic  quadruplets. One zygote giving rise to four identical beings."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/iFDOX.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4216,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4216/ram-manohar-m","reputation":789,"display_name":"Ram Manohar M","accept_rate":31},"score":0,"post_id":10546,"edited":false,"creation_date":1380092120,"comment_id":14034,"body":"The clarification that I require is whether the identical twins are exactly similar or are they mirror images? That is if there is hair whorl on the left side in one, wh